## HashSet.has() method

Returns a boolean asserting whether an element is present with the given value in the hash set or not.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
has(element: E): boolean;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  element | E | The value to test for presence in the hash set. |

<b>Returns:</b>
